article.description: — Zach Scott had 23 points as McNeese State defeated Northwestern State 93-84 on Saturday.
article.headline: Scott carries McNeese St. past Northwestern St. 93-84
article.linkText: Scott carries McNeese St. past Northwestern St. 93-84
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. -- — Zach Scott had 23 points as McNeese State defeated Northwestern State 93-84 on Saturday. Christian Shumate had 19 points, eight rebounds and three blocks for McNeese State (9-15, 4-6 Southland Conference). Brendan Medley-Bacon added 12 points. Johnathan Massie had 12 points, seven rebounds and six assists. Kendal Coleman had 16 points for the Demons (7-17, 4-6) as did Carvell Teasett. LaTerrance Reed had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
